I need to hear you say it
right now.

838
01:23:08,624 --> 01:23:10,865
Yes. Deeply.

839
01:23:11,865 --> 01:23:14,385
More than myself. But I'm lost.

840
01:23:15,945 --> 01:23:17,546
Then let me help you.

841
01:23:17,906 --> 01:23:19,506
You don't deserve this.

842
01:23:19,706 --> 01:23:22,026
Why not? I'm your girlfriend,

843
01:23:22,906 --> 01:23:25,027
and I love you more than myself.

844
01:23:25,147 --> 01:23:27,787
Come on, it's obvious.
You're draining my life away.

845
01:23:27,947 --> 01:23:31,268
I'm doing all I can to get back,
and accept myself,

846
01:23:31,468 --> 01:23:33,188
but if I can't,

847
01:23:33,748 --> 01:23:35,508
don't wait for me.

848
01:23:37,308 --> 01:23:39,149
I wouldn't, either.

849
01:23:40,829 --> 01:23:42,309
What happened to you?

850
01:23:47,870 --> 01:23:49,870
Belén, it's Elena.

851
01:23:51,871 --> 01:23:52,951
How are you?

852
01:23:54,671 --> 01:23:55,951
It's real hot here.

853
01:23:56,151 --> 01:23:58,631
Why don't you come out?
The sea will do you good

854
01:23:58,832 --> 01:24:01,512
I have a guesthouse
for the whole summer.

855
01:24:01,872 --> 01:24:05,272
I'll have a room free in August.
Upstairs.

856
01:24:05,592 --> 01:24:07,873
My best room.
You'll watch the sunset

857
01:24:08,033 --> 01:24:10,913
from your bed.
Bring someone if you want.

858
01:24:11,513 --> 01:24:12,393
Well?

859
01:24:12,794 --> 01:24:15,834
The truth is,
I'd love to visit an island...

860
01:24:17,434 --> 01:24:18,554
with someone.

861
01:24:18,994 --> 01:24:20,155
Then that's it

862
01:24:21,635 --> 01:24:23,915
- It's difficult, Elena.
- Difficult?

863
01:24:24,115 --> 01:24:27,276
Nothing is here
All the bad's left behind

864
01:24:27,476 --> 01:24:29,756
- Just bring along the good
- Right.

865
01:24:31,316 --> 01:24:32,556
The good up front.

866
01:24:33,436 --> 01:24:34,957
I really want to see you,

867
01:24:35,157 --> 01:24:36,077
but here

868
01:24:37,157 --> 01:24:38,997
I don't want to lose touch

869
01:24:41,398 --> 01:24:42,878
Say you'll come

870
01:24:43,878 --> 01:24:44,958
Promise me

871
01:24:47,398 --> 01:24:48,479
I promise.

872
01:24:48,999 --> 01:24:50,199
I'll try.

873
01:24:51,319 --> 01:24:52,399
Good bye.

874
01:25:24,204 --> 01:25:26,964
Forgive me, Lucía.
I've got to end this.

875
01:25:28,964 --> 01:25:32,05
I'm going to kill them
for once and for all.

876
01:25:32,685 --> 01:25:33,725
Both of them.

877
01:25:35,645 --> 01:25:36,645
Right now.

878
01:25:55,648 --> 01:25:58,569
If you've stopped being a writer,
you have to

879
01:25:58,769 --> 01:25:59,849
explain why.

880
01:26:02,089 --> 01:26:03,209
You're holding back.

881
01:26:08,050 --> 01:26:09,130
If you don't tell me,

882
01:26:09,330 --> 01:26:10,570
I'll never forgive you!

883
01:26:10,770 --> 01:26:12,211
You hear me? Never!

884
01:26:12,611 --> 01:26:13,771
I can't talk like this.

885
01:26:13,971 --> 01:26:14,851
Talk?

886
01:26:16,371 --> 01:26:18,852
You're the one who won't talk.

887
01:26:19,812 --> 01:26:21,652
You keep it all inside.

888
01:26:21,812 --> 01:26:23,772
You won't let me help you.

889
01:26:24,212 --> 01:26:25,452
Everything's you.

890
01:26:25,612 --> 01:26:27,413
I'm crumpled up in the corner.

891
01:26:28,373 --> 01:26:29,293
Look.

892
01:26:29,613 --> 01:26:31,213
You were meant to live alone,

893
01:26:32,854 --> 01:26:34,094
and to suffer alone.

894
01:26:34,934 --> 01:26:38,414
And to drive yourself fucking crazy,
which I don't understand.

895
01:26:39,214 --> 01:26:40,895
You're sick, Lorenzo.

896
01:26:41,335 --> 01:26:45,735
Sick of yourself, of your
own standards, and nothing else.

897
01:26:46,455 --> 01:26:48,096
Of your fucking secrets!

898
01:26:48,536 --> 01:26:51,056
You keep me around,
but in the dark.

899
01:26:52,216 --> 01:26:54,017
Because my complaints
don't count.

900
01:26:54,777 --> 01:26:56,137
Because you don't give

901
01:26:56,297 --> 01:26:58,137
a fuck what happens to me.

902
01:26:58,297 --> 01:27:00,057
Your troubles are so deep,

903
01:27:00,457 --> 01:27:01,938
I'm fucking stupid,

904
01:27:02,138 --> 01:27:04,818
and all you care about
is if I screw my boss or not.

905
01:27:10,739 --> 01:27:12,099
I'm exhausted.

906
01:27:13,019 --> 01:27:14,379
You're driving me nuts.

907
01:27:14,699 --> 01:27:16,300
I'll be late to work.

908
01:27:18,900 --> 01:27:20,260
Enjoy your hole.

909
01:27:22,301 --> 01:27:24,461
Have fun rotting by yourself.

910
01:27:32,862 --> 01:27:35,182
Look, I've never been this mean

911
01:27:35,382 --> 01:27:36,583
to anyone.

912
01:27:37,743 --> 01:27:40,023
It's the last time
I'll let myself talk like this.

913
01:27:40,543 --> 01:27:42,183
It's for me, not you.

914
01:27:45,664 --> 01:27:46,744
That's right.

915
01:27:48,704 --> 01:27:50,825
It's time to think of myself,

916
01:27:51,345 --> 01:27:52,745
of my own needs.

917
01:27:53,905 --> 01:27:56,345
Because I see no future with you.

918
01:28:46,153 --> 01:28:46,873
Lucía!

919
01:28:49,433 --> 01:28:51,633
Come over here
and lie next to me.

920
01:29:23,158 --> 01:29:24,678
Relax, Lucía.

921
01:29:25,318 --> 01:29:27,839
Let the mud absorb all the bad.

922
01:29:28,199 --> 01:29:31,079
Later it'll wash away in the sea.

923
01:30:05,324 --> 01:30:06,604
I don't want sex.

924
01:30:09,04 --> 01:30:10,485
I'm not ready yet.

925
01:30:20,206 --> 01:30:21,446
Don't worry.

926
01:30:24,207 --> 01:30:26,247
We'll just lie here,

927
01:30:28,367 --> 01:30:30,127
drying out in the sun.

928
01:30:39,569 --> 01:30:41,649
Yeah, he looks like Carlos.

929
01:30:49,370 --> 01:30:52,171
"Missing for 6 months".

930
01:30:52,691 --> 01:30:54,811
"Manuela and Belén Lozano,
mother and daughter,

931
01:30:55,011 --> 01:30:57,771
and Antonio Castillo,
were all living together.

932
01:30:57,971 --> 01:31:02,332
If anyone knows where they are,
please contact the police."

933
01:31:02,812 --> 01:31:03,852
The police?

934
01:31:03,972 --> 01:31:05,172
We'll...

935
01:31:05,812 --> 01:31:07,613
act like we didn't see this,

936
01:31:08,373 --> 01:31:10,093
Like nothing's happened.

937
01:31:14,654 --> 01:31:16,494
We know he lived with two women.

938
01:31:16,894 --> 01:31:18,414
Mother and daughter.

939
01:31:18,614 --> 01:31:20,255
Yeah, and the daughter...

940
01:31:22,295 --> 01:31:23,135
What?

941
01:31:25,055 --> 01:31:27,736
The daughter was taking care of...

942
01:31:28,376 --> 01:31:29,616
my daughter.

943
01:31:40,257 --> 01:31:42,258
They left without him,

944
01:31:42,618 --> 01:31:44,898
quietly, without saying good bye

945
01:31:45,258 --> 01:31:47,138
As he slept,

946
01:31:47,298 --> 01:31:48,539
Like in a dream

947
01:31:49,019 --> 01:31:51,619
When he woke, he felt
the two lifeless women

948
01:31:52,299 --> 01:31:53,619
were still with him,

949
01:31:54,459 --> 01:31:55,740
Like any morning

950
01:31:56,220 --> 01:31:57,460
at that hour

951
01:31:58,140 --> 01:32:00,740
And he lay still,
wishing his life would also

952
01:32:00,940 --> 01:32:03,861
leave him, through his blood

953
01:32:04,541 --> 01:32:06,661
What good was his blood now?

954
01:32:07,661 --> 01:32:10,142
He wished it softly,
without real intent

955
01:32:10,982 --> 01:32:13,062
And he chose to escape,
to start over,

956
01:32:13,542 --> 01:32:14,662
to be new

957
01:32:14,862 --> 01:32:16,663
To change his blood

958
01:32:16,863 --> 01:32:18,183
So he said good bye

959
01:32:18,943 --> 01:32:19,863
and left

960
01:32:24,104 --> 01:32:25,944
We should give him a chance.

961
01:32:28,104 --> 01:32:29,945
Don't we all deserve one?

962
01:32:32,225 --> 01:32:33,985
Just in case, if in doubt,

963
01:32:35,025 --> 01:32:37,146
isn't it better to trust people?

964
01:32:37,666 --> 01:32:38,586
Right?

965
01:32:41,666 --> 01:32:44,547
So when he gets back,
we'll ask him to explain.

966
01:32:45,187 --> 01:32:46,587
It's better this way.

967
01:32:47,347 --> 01:32:49,507
- Especially for you.
- For me?

968
01:32:50,147 --> 01:32:52,028
I just want to forget.

969
01:32:53,388 --> 01:32:55,228
You can't forget some things.

970
01:32:55,348 --> 01:32:58,429
In this house you can.
That's why we're here.

971
01:32:59,949 --> 01:33:01,309
Then it's too late.

972
01:33:02,349 --> 01:33:04,509
I should have come before.

973
01:33:05,910 --> 01:33:07,270
When there was time...

974
01:33:10,510 --> 01:33:11,550
for Lorenzo.

975
01:33:14,471 --> 01:33:16,871
I wanted him to show me
the island.

976
01:33:17,871 --> 01:33:20,352
I asked him to, but he wouldn't.

977
01:33:22,992 --> 01:33:25,232
It would have been
his birthday soon.

978
01:33:30,633 --> 01:33:32,833
- What day?
- The 23rd.

979
01:33:43,315 --> 01:33:44,115
Of May?

980
01:33:50,236 --> 01:33:51,956
We could have celebrated

981
01:33:52,276 --> 01:33:53,636
here on the island.

982
01:33:53,877 --> 01:33:54,957
Maybe even with you.

983
01:33:56,317 --> 01:33:57,357
Who knows if

984
01:33:57,557 --> 01:33:59,437
we'd have met, right?

985
01:34:00,157 --> 01:34:01,038
Right.

986
01:34:03,798 --> 01:34:05,158
When was Lorenzo here?

987
01:34:07,118 --> 01:34:08,399
A long time ago.

988
01:34:09,759 --> 01:34:11,239
Before we met.

989
01:34:11,599 --> 01:34:12,679
How long ago?

990
01:34:13,119 --> 01:34:15,520
About six years ago.

991
01:34:17,440 --> 01:34:18,400
Yeah.

992
01:34:18,640 --> 01:34:20,080
I think he turned 25 here.

993
01:34:21,921 --> 01:34:22,801
Lucía...

994
01:34:24,281 --> 01:34:25,201
What is it?

995
01:34:27,481 --> 01:34:28,962
I'm overwhelmed...

996
01:34:29,362 --> 01:34:31,162
But I can't cry.

997
01:34:32,322 --> 01:34:33,362
Don't worry.

998
01:34:33,762 --> 01:34:35,322
You don't have to.

999
01:34:36,163 --> 01:34:38,443
I'm the one
who should cry over him.

1000
01:34:46,164 --> 01:34:47,564
I'll just faint, then.

1001
01:34:49,925 --> 01:34:51,085
It's the sea.

1002
01:34:51,645 --> 01:34:53,365
Must be high tide.

1003
01:35:04,727 --> 01:35:06,367
I'll never cry again.

1004
01:35:10,327 --> 01:35:11,648
I'm going to bed.

1005
01:35:22,489 --> 01:35:23,569
What's going on?

1006
01:36:08,496 --> 01:36:09,736
"Luna,

1007
01:36:09,936 --> 01:36:12,056
spring of 1988".

1008
01:36:16,297 --> 01:36:17,217
Luna.

1009
01:36:28,739 --> 01:36:31,179
"Why bother being a father

1010
01:36:31,939 --> 01:36:33,419
if she didn't know?"

1011
01:36:35,340 --> 01:36:37,860
He knew then that
if he'd told her,

1012
01:36:38,580 --> 01:36:40,740
she'd have kept the secret

1013
01:36:45,741 --> 01:36:47,821
Lucía, never talk to me
about this.

1014
01:36:48,341 --> 01:36:50,142
I don't want to hear it.

1015
01:37:02,503 --> 01:37:03,584
Well, I do.

1016
01:38:02,992 --> 01:38:04,392
He's out diving.

1017
01:38:06,833 --> 01:38:08,233
Beneath the island.

1018
01:38:10,993 --> 01:38:12,393
Do you like Carlos?

1019
01:38:14,234 --> 01:38:15,634
I don't anymore.

1020
01:38:16,154 --> 01:38:19,834
Go ahead, he's all yours.
I won't even be jealous.

1021
01:38:24,915 --> 01:38:26,235
What are you doing?

1022
01:38:28,116 --> 01:38:29,836
Asking a friend for advice.

1023
01:38:30,036 --> 01:38:31,356
I don't know him,

1024
01:38:31,636 --> 01:38:33,676
but I'm getting to like him.

1025
01:38:39,557 --> 01:38:42,878
He's been writing me since
I got here. He made up

1026
01:38:43,078 --> 01:38:45,198
a sweet story to help me.

1027
01:38:45,598 --> 01:38:47,438
He taught me to forget.

1028
01:38:47,638 --> 01:38:49,079
And to escape pain.

1029
01:38:51,999 --> 01:38:53,039
Want to read it?

1030
01:38:54,279 --> 01:38:55,520
You could get into it.

1031
01:38:56,200 --> 01:38:58,240
It's full of advantages.

1032
01:38:59,040 --> 01:39:00,080
Because in the end...

1033
01:39:00,600 --> 01:39:01,680
there's a hole

1034
01:39:02,121 --> 01:39:04,081
to escape through.

1035
01:39:10,202 --> 01:39:11,442
Back to the middle.

1036
01:39:13,402 --> 01:39:15,162
To change course,

1037
01:39:16,443 --> 01:39:17,443
if you want.

1038
01:39:24,324 --> 01:39:27,604
That's his icon,
it's a lighthouse.

1039
01:39:29,644 --> 01:39:31,685
But it has no keeper,

1040
01:39:32,605 --> 01:39:34,645
it must be a computer.

1041
01:39:36,205 --> 01:39:37,446
Maybe his.

1042
01:39:45,087 --> 01:39:47,127
You'll meet my daughter.

1043
01:39:52,128 --> 01:39:53,528
I can't read this.

1044
01:39:53,888 --> 01:39:54,888
Why not?

1045
01:39:59,529 --> 01:40:01,369
It will grab me.

1046
01:40:02,249 --> 01:40:03,729
And won't let go.

1047
01:40:04,209 --> 01:40:05,450
That's good.

1048
01:40:07,010 --> 01:40:08,650
Did you finally do it?

1049
01:40:08,930 --> 01:40:10,010
Do what?

1050
01:40:10,250 --> 01:40:11,610
Change course?

1051
01:40:13,171 --> 01:40:16,051
Not all the way,
there wasn't time.

1052
01:40:16,931 --> 01:40:18,531
That's why I'm writing him.

1053
01:40:20,972 --> 01:40:23,452
WHERE'S THE KEEPER?

1054
01:40:24,692 --> 01:40:25,892
Don't write him.

1055
01:40:29,333 --> 01:40:32,093
There's nothing more he can do.

1056
01:40:40,615 --> 01:40:43,615
Has he written you
since I first got here?

1057
01:41:48,824 --> 01:41:51,625
Hi, Lorenzo. How are you?

1058
01:41:53,265 --> 01:41:54,905
Your face says it all.

1059
01:41:55,065 --> 01:41:57,266
They called to say
you were more awake.

1060
01:42:00,786 --> 01:42:02,026
Do you know who I am?

1061
01:42:03,346 --> 01:42:04,107
Pepe.

1062
01:42:05,587 --> 01:42:06,707
Thank God.

1063
01:42:09,467 --> 01:42:12,908
Glad to have you back.
You'll be writing in no time.

1064
01:42:14,548 --> 01:42:15,788
Where's Lucía?

1065
01:42:20,869 --> 01:42:22,389
It says here that

1066
01:42:22,749 --> 01:42:25,150
your cranial hematoma
has subsided.

1067
01:42:25,750 --> 01:42:29,230
And the rest of your bruises
are history.

1068
01:42:30,630 --> 01:42:31,670
Where's Lucía?

1069
01:42:36,151 --> 01:42:37,871
You were in bad shape.

1070
01:42:39,552 --> 01:42:41,872
We didn't think you'd make it.

1071
01:42:43,672 --> 01:42:44,832
How long have I been here?

1072
01:42:45,912 --> 01:42:46,913
Well...

1073
01:42:48,473 --> 01:42:50,273
One week in a coma,

1074
01:42:50,873 --> 01:42:53,114
with this horrible respirator...

1075
01:42:53,594 --> 01:42:55,314
And two more weeks

1076
01:42:55,754 --> 01:42:58,834
breathing on your own,
but unconscious.

1077
01:42:59,714 --> 01:43:03,075
And in this room
since four or five days ago,

1078
01:43:04,235 --> 01:43:06,515
blabbering in your sleep.

1079
01:43:06,955 --> 01:43:09,796
And when you'd wake up,
you were out of it.

1080
01:43:15,037 --> 01:43:17,437
We haven't heard from Lucía.

1081
01:43:18,117 --> 01:43:20,117
I looked everywhere.

1082
01:43:20,477 --> 01:43:24,118
She hasn't been to your place,
nor the restaurant, since the night

1083
01:43:24,318 --> 01:43:25,318
of your accident.

1084
01:43:33,279 --> 01:43:34,239
Lorenzo.

1085
01:43:36,040 --> 01:43:39,160
I think Lucía
believes you're dead.

1086
01:43:40,240 --> 01:43:41,640
That's why she left.

1087
01:43:41,840 --> 01:43:43,481
I talked to the ambulance guy.

1088
01:43:44,161 --> 01:43:46,441
He said a cop called your house

1089
01:43:46,641 --> 01:43:47,881
and talked to her.

1090
01:43:48,081 --> 01:43:49,922
He mentioned the car

1091
01:43:50,242 --> 01:43:51,322
and she hung up.

1092
01:43:52,802 --> 01:43:54,082
He tried to call back

1093
01:43:55,242 --> 01:43:56,643
but she wouldn't answer.

1094
01:43:58,803 --> 01:44:00,123
I need to pee.

1095
01:44:01,203 --> 01:44:02,363
Do it there,

1096
01:44:02,563 --> 01:44:04,444
- in the pan.
- No way!

1097
01:44:04,684 --> 01:44:05,804
Wait, wait.

1098
01:44:06,244 --> 01:44:08,484
Thanks, Pepe, but I can manage.

1099
01:44:11,685 --> 01:44:13,405
Lose the attitude.

1100
01:44:13,645 --> 01:44:15,965
I've helped you all week.

1101
01:44:16,405 --> 01:44:17,926
You just don't remember.

1102
01:44:35,128 --> 01:44:36,488
I know where she might be.

1103
01:44:39,209 --> 01:44:40,249
You came by car?

1104
01:44:41,969 --> 01:44:43,569
As soon as they called.

1105
01:45:09,213 --> 01:45:10,293
Good morning.

1106
01:45:11,253 --> 01:45:13,894
Tell me right now why
you're here and Belén isn't.

1107
01:45:16,854 --> 01:45:17,894
You see?

1108
01:45:18,094 --> 01:45:21,295
I don't want to forget anymore.
Thanks to you, honey.

1109
01:45:24,175 --> 01:45:25,095
Well?

1110
01:45:25,775 --> 01:45:27,216
Won't you answer me?

1111
01:45:28,816 --> 01:45:32,296
It's time to show you who
I really am, no more stories.

1112
01:45:32,536 --> 01:45:35,377
Were you there with Belén,
in my room,

1113
01:45:38,737 --> 01:45:41,578
when that fucking dog
killed my daughter?

1114
01:45:42,978 --> 01:45:44,698
- It wasn't me.
- It wasn't?

1115
01:45:44,898 --> 01:45:47,658
Then why are the cops
looking for you?

1116
01:45:51,219 --> 01:45:52,819
Belén was with some guy

1117
01:45:53,019 --> 01:45:56,020
who met her in the park
with your daughter.

1118
01:45:57,140 --> 01:46:00,620
But he disappeared
after that night.

1119
01:46:11,142 --> 01:46:12,302
What about Belén?

1120
01:46:12,502 --> 01:46:14,582
Where is she?
Since you know everything.

1121
01:46:16,063 --> 01:46:19,223
She left with her mom
but didn't tell me where.

1122
01:46:20,543 --> 01:46:23,664
She changed in the end,
and chose her mom over me.

1123
01:46:28,664 --> 01:46:30,065
Can't blame her.

1124
01:46:30,745 --> 01:46:33,185
A mother always comes first.

1125
01:46:36,505 --> 01:46:39,826
I don't trust you anymore,
Antonio...

1126
01:46:41,306 --> 01:46:43,746
I won't ask you
any more questions.

1127
01:46:43,946 --> 01:46:45,787
I'll leave that to the police.

1128
01:46:46,427 --> 01:46:48,227
Lying to them won't be so easy.

1129
01:46:49,307 --> 01:46:51,668
Look how brave I got
all of a sudden.

1130
01:46:52,028 --> 01:46:52,708
Wait.

1131
01:46:54,108 --> 01:46:56,988
Please don't call the police.

1132
01:46:57,988 --> 01:46:59,029
Why not?

1133
01:46:59,549 --> 01:47:01,469
Are you holding back
anything else?

1134
01:47:05,030 --> 01:47:06,390
I've no one left

1135
01:47:07,150 --> 01:47:08,550
who I can trust.

1136
01:47:10,030 --> 01:47:11,390
Where are you going?

1137
01:47:11,870 --> 01:47:13,191
Making a getaway?

1138
01:47:13,391 --> 01:47:15,191
